parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The shoe getting caught on the underside of the brake pedal can cause unexpected braking issues, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels stuck or caught

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vehicle's tendency to pull to one side or drift while braking can cause accidents, loss of control, or difficulty stopping.
symptoms: Vehicle pulls to one side while braking
drifts to one side while braking

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brakes during emergency stopping can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: no response from the anti-lock device

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause loss of braking effectiveness, leading to accidents or injuries.
The failure of the brakes in certain weather conditions can cause accidents, loss of control, or difficulty stopping.
symptoms: Brakes lockup in icy or snowy conditions
brakes fail to stop the vehicle in damp weather

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat frame and seatback can cause the seat to collapse, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries to the driver and passengers.
symptoms: the seat doesn't lock back into position
and the driver or passenger is thrown backwards.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine compartment fires can cause significant damage to the vehicle and potentially lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: smoke or flames visible under the hood.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical Short in Brake Light Unit
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An electrical short in the brake light unit can cause the brake lights to malfunction, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Brake lights do not function properly

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Intermittent engine shut down can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: occurs at low to highway speeds (40-55mph)

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The incompatibility of the driver-side airbag and horn can lead to reduced safety features and potentially cause accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Horn does not function due to design issue with driver-side airbag.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rollaway Vehicle Due to Transmission Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vehicle rolling backwards without warning can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially if the vehicle is on an incline or in a crowded area.
symptoms: The vehicle starts to roll backwards without warning
and can only be stopped by applying the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission hesitation and slipping can cause loss of control, accidents, and damage to the transmission and other components.
symptoms: The transmission hesitates or slips when shifting from park to forward gears
resulting in a loss of power and control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission noise and leaks can cause damage to the transmission and other components, leading to costly repairs and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: is heard when coming to a stop
and transmission fluid leaks can cause a fire while driving.
